caption.text:
Seven days of #kookievision, based on my latest Link's Awakening sugar cookie set. Day seven - the final day. Link. I saved our hero for last, of course. I kind of dig the new look that they gave him in the newly reimagined Link's Awakening. It's got this cute shiny toy appearance. I saw the new Amiibo figure of him (which I don't even collect), but I might have to snatch him up. Which was your favourite sugar cookie of the set?

If you want to see more, I created a 20 minute video compilation of the entire set. No instructions, no dialogue, just some music. Check out "Kookievision" on the Sweethart Baking Experiment YouTube channel to watch it.

For my favourite sugar cookie dough and royal icing recipe, visit the "How To" section of my website at sweethartbaking.com.

Do you love my cookie videos and want to see more? Check me out on Ko-Fi to make a small coffee-sized Paypal donation towards the future of Kookievision:
☕ ko-fi.com/sweethart

Music is "Powerup!" by Jeremy Blake from the YouTube audio library.

Cloud Strife, Some Dedication To How Amazing Clouds Remake Design Is Looking; Final Fantasy VII Sample Square Preview Extra / Siggraph 95 Works & Final Fantasy VII Remake Exclusive Cloud Cover For PlayStation Magazine UK.
.
It’s crazy to see how far Final Fantasy VII has actually come all way from 1997 to 2019 when you really compare them next to eachother with an original early render to the Remake CGI next to it really highlights how amazing Clouds design is looking 👌🏻 .
Here is one of FFVIIs most earliest Renders to What will be its most recent next March. I love this original render for Cloud outside the Shinra building where there was minor changes made example being the buster sword design itself where was changed before the finalised Cover Artwork for the US box art which as you know the Remake cover art replicates now.
.

La #MilanGamesWeek 2019, LA fiera Italiana del settore videoludico volge oggi al termine.

Rappresentare #Nintendo su un palco è un’emozione indescrivibile. Incontrare tanti colleghi e personaggi unici è incredibile, così com’è incredibile incontrare molti di voi e salutarvi nello stand dedicato. 
Con questo post vorrei augurare un grazie di cuore a chi ha creduto a questo progetto e chi mi ha permesso di arrivare fino a qui. Trovate qualche foto scattata oggi qui sotto nella galleria 😍🙏🏻 Grazie a Nintendo, voi amici e ai colleghi che rendono tutta questa esperienza unica e indimenticabile. Al prossimo anno!

caption.text:
How to get the Samsung Fortnite Glow skin:

You’ll first need to have Fornite installed on your Samsung device. You can get the game from the Galaxy Store or the Galaxy Game Launcher. Then either sign in to your Epic Games account or sign up for a new account.

Head over to the Store and you’ll see the Fortnite Glow skin in the Store under Limited Time Offers. Ensure that the store is set to Samsung in Settings > Account > Content > Android Store Selection. You will then see a screen which asks you to register a credit card if you haven’t done so already. Go ahead and register a credit card, don’t worry, it won’t be charged.

Tap on the Fortnite Glow skin again and then either choose to redeem the outfit and the emote for yourself or gift it to a friend. Be sure to do this before December 31, 2019. If you choose to redeem it for yourself, the Samsung Fortnite Glow skin is going to be available in your Locker.

Eligible Samsung devices include the Galaxy Note 10 and Galaxy Note 10+/10+ 5G, Galaxy Note 9 and Note 8, Galaxy S10e, S10, S10+ and S10 5G, Galaxy S9/S9+, Galaxy S8/S8+ and S8 Active, Galaxy S7, S7 edge and S7 Active, Galaxy A9, Galaxy A70, A80 and A90. The Galaxy Tab S6, Tab S4 and S3 are eligible as well.

caption.text:
I guess this is what I'm calling an impromptu Wedding Weekend Haul! My beautiful sister got married this weekend (!!!), and it was honestly one of the most wonderful, amazing, and joyful experiences of my life. And whenever I'm in a new place, I like to check out the local bookstore scene and buy books (and video games I guess lol) as momentos of my trip!
💫
This is what I came home with, the stories that will forever remind me of this whirlwind weekend. What better way to commemorate love and joy than with a finished copy of HOW TO BE REMY CAMERON by @wintersjulian? What better way to remind myself that exciting things lie ahead in the future than volume 21 of MY HERO ACADEMIA? What better way to remind myself that it's okay to take time for myself than with ZELDA: LINK'S AWAKENING? I'm so glad that these are the stories I chose to take with me, carry with me in my heart, and mark this occasion.
💫
Now I'm refreshed, excited, and looking forward to what comes next with an open heart! My birthday is next Saturday, October 5th, and I'm ready to put the wedding stress behind me and live my fullest, most unapologetic life 🎉🎉🎉 I hope you all had a wonderful weekend yourselves and that there are exciting things ahead for all of you as well! 💕
-------------------------

caption.text: Yoshi Spike Sunday‼️‼️‼️

I'll have another review up tomorrow hopefully but for now I'd like to recommend another indie game to you all. SUPERHOT is a fantastic first person shooter with one simple gimmick.

Time only moves when you move.

This leads to some pretty tense situations and even if you're not a shooter fan, I'd still recommend it because it feels like a puzzle game in some instances. Definitely give it a go if you've never played it before. It's the most innovative shooter I've played in years.

caption.text:
A little while ago, the law firm of Chimicles Schwartz Kriner & Donaldson-Smith announced that they were filing a class-action lawsuit against Nintendo due to Joy-Con drift. The law firm was going to investigate the issue to see if there were legal grounds for compensation from Nintendo to anyone who had experienced the issue.
.
Per IGN, the law firm has amended its class-action lawsuit for everyone that has purchased a Nintendo Switch, a Switch Lite, and separate Joy-Con controllers. This is the law firm’s statement: “The Amended Complaint alleges that the Joy-Con controllers are defective, leading to a phenomenon known as ‘drift.'” The Amended Complaint also claims that Joy-Cons are in breach of warranty, fraud, and “violations of numerous state consumer protection statutes.”
.

.

Mais um #TbT da BGS 2018.
.
.
A Brasil Game Show 2018 me marcou de diversas formas por ser minha primeira BGS. Mas, este dia me marcou ainda mais por ter a oportunidade de levar meu filho, @matheussvieira08, que é autista.
.
.
Somente quem tem um filho autista sabe a dificuldade, não por ele ser autista mas sim pela ignorância e preconceito das pessoas ao redor, inclusive daquelas que se dizem "amigos". Um dos momentos que mais vi a alegria de meu filho, foi quando fomos conhecer o lendário dublador de Super Mário Bros,  Charles Martinet.
.
.
@charlesmartinetitsame obrigado por todo o carinho, atenção e alegria prestados a mim e ao meu filho. É uma lembrança e realização que, com certeza, nunca iremos esquecer. Foi uma honra conhecê-lo. Obrigado pelas palavras  e autógrafo no chapéu Mário Bros do meu filho. Nunca o esqueceremos.
.
.

preview_comments.text: Exatamente @wiilingtonfox, fico muito decepcionado em comprar jogos de PS4 físico por exemplo, pra mim não valem (literalmente) o preço que cobram. Nem uma arte na parte de trás da capa colocam, pior, colocam os termos de garantia impressos ali, coisa mais horrível. Eu fico feliz e triste com essa situação, triste porque é o fim de uma era infelizmente, mas feliz porque agora posso me concentrar na coleção de jogos até o Switch e portáteis (que não é pouca coisa) e de resto "economizo". 😆

caption.text: Como um aficionado pelo gênero de jogos de corrida, este título não poderia ficar de fora da minha coleção. Um dos melhores exemplos de como unir o saudosismo a tecnologia mais atual, a equipe da @aquirisgs realmente fez um trabalho brilhante neste título, que merece todos os méritos. E esta edição é mais do que especial, uma bela homenagem aos fãs de todo o mundo.

caption.text:
Cuphead - Celebrates 5 Million Copies Sold, 2nd Anniversary, & 20% Off☕🎂
-
Studio MDHR is celebrating two big milestones for Cuphead being that the game is now two years old since its inital release back on the Xbox One on September 29th, 2017. Along with this, it's also celebrating selling 5 million copies.
-
Finally, in celebration of all this news, the game will be 20% on all digital platforms, including on the Nintendo Switch eShop until October 6th.
-
🐦》Studio MDHR's Tweet:
Cuphead turns two today, and we're so humbled to announce: it has officially gone five-times platinum!! Starting now, the game is 20% off on all platforms for a full week. And stay tuned, because we have 5 days of fun and giveaways planned to celebrate 5 million copies sold!
--
🐦》NoA's Tweet:
Happy Birthday, Cuphead!

Today’s the perfect day to cut some cake and wallop some baddies, because @StudioMDHR’s all-cartoon wondergame Cuphead is 20% off on #NintendoSwitch #eShop from now till 10/6!
--
• ( Source: Studio MDHR & Nintendo of America on Twitter )
